{
  "article_id": "Hardacre1879",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The story briefly is this. Each fact corroberated personally by a research covering thirty years."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "living alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the Santa Barbara Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for over eighteen years, was found by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a party of seal hunters",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in 1853."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She died shortly after, and her country has never been established."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It has been supposed that she was an Indian from the fact that "
      },
      {
        "text": "thirty Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", comprising the total population, had been removed from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in 1835 [...] and brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sgabriel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to work in the mission be instructed by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission Fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "One of the residents",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "A woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "jumped overboard during the confusion of embarking and returned to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "[.]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The storm necessitated the her [...] at that time, and [...] ("
      },
      {
        "text": "the only one on the coast",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ") [...] [...] after landing [...] [...] the next trip to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "thereby preventing the intended search for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the missing woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[...] for fifteen years—no boat could be secured to take the rescue journey of seventy miles. out of the [...] of traffic The gold and excitement brought sailors and craft to "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", so that and in 1851, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a mission father of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", by the payment of two hundred dollars, induced succeeded in sending a [...] craft to search "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The father",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had never ceased his prayers that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the abandoned one",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "might be preserved until help reached her—but as year after year passed, the probability of her death, was accepted by all those who knew the circumstances. [...] "
      },
      {
        "text": "The Captain",
        "entity_key": "tje",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "reported that he found no trace of occupation of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and thus the matter was settled. His reports of fine otter fishing in the vicinity of "
      },
      {
        "text": "this [...] island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and [...] [...] "
      },
      {
        "text": "unknown island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", [...] our "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to go with "
      },
      {
        "text": "his own boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "a crew of [...] Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "the following year as an otter hunt. Their camp was made on the beach, and they worked busily for six weeks, secured a cargo of pelts, and in the midst of a at the approach of a [...] storm, they made haste to shelter in the lee of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The sailors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "reported that from the [...], "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "ran up and down the along the edge of a cliff, in the pelting storm, and beconed beckoned as they left anchorage—the sheets of rain hid her from plain view—It was supposed to be the ghost of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman who perished there",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The following year "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "went again to the otter grounds.—Camped in the same spot. Having no occasion to explore the precipitous heights of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—they [...] thus remained close to shore, and as they"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "There is a doubt in my own mind, whether "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was Indian. There is a rumor that a very short time before "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was depopulated, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was cast ashore from a wreck, and that shortly after she gave birth to "
      },
      {
        "text": "a child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". This information has reached me since the material was gathered for my article as originally published. The search for facts, was undertaken with by four persons [...]"
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr[.] Dimmick",
        "entity_key": "ldi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[,] "
      },
      {
        "text": "Henry Chapman",
        "entity_key": "hfo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[, ...] artist, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "James Calkins",
        "entity_key": "jcalkins",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", [...] all three residing in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—and now deceased. They interested me in the subject, and by interpreters all the Spanish and Indian residents of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barabara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in [...] 1853 and previous were interrogated. At that time (1879) the "
      },
      {
        "text": "principal actors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in the rescue were living. As I sifted the material the doubt arose in my mind as to her "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "being a native Islander. Her manner of meeting "
      },
      {
        "text": "her rescuers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was not that of a wild woman, but of one who had knowledge of the amenities of life—Her entrance into white civilized homes, was not that of a creature utterly unfamiliar with house conveniences—her tact in meeting strangers, receiving their gifts politely, and after they were gone—distributing them among the children of "
      },
      {
        "text": "her host",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Her conversing continuously in a tongue unkown to any—but evidently a language with which she was thoroughly familiar—no hesitation—or forgotten phrases—no one of the various Indian tribes obtainable could understand one word she uttered—A search was made for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the people from San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but they were scattered over the country, and were never located. They were simply "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "—She told her story by expressive pantomime—and what seemed to be an account of shipwreck—[...]—and looking for rescue—the pictures on the walls of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the cave",
        "entity_key": "re_lwcave",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ]
  ]
}